&lt;p&gt;
MEN1611 is a potent and selective phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase (PI3K) inhibitor with a novel chemical structure targeting the α, β and γ isoforms while sparing the δ, with a novel chemical structure.
&lt;br /&gt;The PI3K/Akt pathway regulates various cellular processes such as proliferation, growth, apoptosis and cytoskeletal rearrangement. Various types of cancers are thought to be “addicted” to PI3K/Akt pathway signaling and therefore inhibition of PI3K is a potent therapeutic strategy for fighting cancer.
&lt;br /&gt;MEN1611 is being investigated as a potential treatment for patients with PIK3CA-mutated, HER2-positive, advanced or metastatic breast cancer who have failed anti-HER2 based therapy.
&lt;/p&gt;

