&lt;p&gt;Elacestrant is a selective estrogen receptor degrader (SERD) evaluated for potential use as a once daily oral treatment in patients with estrogen receptor positive (ER+)/HER2- advanced or metastatic breast cancer. Studies completed to date, including the positive results from the EMERALD phase 3 trial, indicate that the compound has the potential for use as a single agent or in combination with other therapies for the treatment of breast cancer. Indeed, Elacestrant has been the first oral SERD to show positive results in a pivotal, phase III trial as a monotherapy versus standard of care for the treatment of ER+/ HER2- advanced or metastatic breast cancer. .&lt;/p&gt;

